text: Cok Istri Agung Sanistyarani (born 31 December 1994) is an Indonesian karateka. In 2018, she won one of the bronze medals in the women's kumite 55 kg event at the 2018 Asian Games held in Jakarta, Indonesia. == Career == In 2013, she won one of the bronze medals in the women's kumite 61kg event at the 2013 Islamic Solidarity Games held in Palembang, Indonesia. In 2014, she competed in the women's kumite 55 kg event at the 2014 Asian Games held in Incheon, South Korea where she lost her bronze medal match against Mae Soriano. At the 2018 Asian Karate Championships held in Amman, Jordan she won the silver medal in the women's kumite 55 kg event.
